# Copy to .env.live and fill in. Never commit .env.live.
#
# LIVE-account credentials ONLY. This file exists because the live engine shares
# a repo - and therefore a .env - with the demo lab, and .env holds the DEMO
# login. Environment variables beat .env (pydantic-settings precedence), so
# infra/run-live-engine.ps1 loads this file and exports these before starting,
# which is what stops the live terminal being told to log into the demo account.
#
# run-live-engine.ps1 refuses to start if any of these is empty. That is
# deliberate: an engine with no account pinned trades whatever account its
# terminal happens to be on, and cannot log back in when that changes. See
# docs/safety-rails.md.
#
# This is NOT a live-trading guard. The four guards are unchanged and all still
# apply (docs/going-live.md); this only ensures the live engine talks to the
# account it says it does.

MT5_LOGIN=
MT5_PASSWORD=
MT5_SERVER=
